{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"NONE","body":"> When changing the texture (map) of a material the object flickers even if the image has already been loaded before. \n\nThat's because your method to change the texture is not the right one.\nUse this method and you won't get any flickering:\nhttp:\/\/necromanthus.com\/Test\/html5\/sims_room.html \n","created_at":"2016-07-15T10:23:03.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9337#issuecomment-232916669","id":232916669,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9337","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIzMjkxNjY2OQ==","updated_at":"2016-07-15T10:23:03.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/232916669","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/10137?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/ghost","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMTM3","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"ghost","type":"User","id":10137,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@mrdumb: Thanks for your reply. So you actually preload every image as texture and then assign it later, right?\n\nIn my application the available textures are depending on the loaded objects and their configuration. There could be 50+ different textures to select and I only want to load the ones the user really wants to assign.\n\nPreviously there was a cache in the ImageLoader which was removed in the mentioned issue\/commit.\nSo I think I would have to create a texture cache in my application to reuse any previously selected texture? Or is there another way that ThreeJS would use cached images\/textures again?\n","created_at":"2016-07-15T11:23:22.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9337#issuecomment-232927317","id":232927317,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9337","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIzMjkyNzMxNw==","updated_at":"2016-07-15T11:23:22.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/232927317","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/6675519?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/oemmes","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY2NzU1MTk=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"oemmes","type":"User","id":6675519,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"NONE","body":"> There could be 50+ different textures to select and I only want to load the ones the user really wants to assign.\n\nThese days most of the computers have 16-64 GB RAM and most of the graphic cards have 2-8 GB VRAM.\nSo preloading is the best approach by far.\n","created_at":"2016-07-15T11:58:13.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9337#issuecomment-232933908","id":232933908,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9337","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIzMjkzMzkwOA==","updated_at":"2016-07-15T11:58:24.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/232933908","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/10137?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/ghost","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMTM3","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"ghost","type":"User","id":10137,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Sorry, but for me it's not suitable to preload all of the textures. Independent from the number of textures I cannot know beforehand which image file matches the configuration.\n\nExample:\nA furniture surface can have a number of different materials. For wood materials the texture\/image file also depends on the graining direction (horizontal\/vertical) - which doubles the texture count.\nActually which image is used for a specific configuration depends on a \"lookup table\" in our application.\n\nAnd besides the (V)RAM amount one would transfer a lot of unnecessary (kilo\/mega)bytes over the client's web connection if all images are preloaded.\n","created_at":"2016-07-15T12:12:58.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9337#issuecomment-232936189","id":232936189,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9337","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIzMjkzNjE4OQ==","updated_at":"2016-07-15T12:12:58.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/232936189","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/6675519?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/oemmes","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY2NzU1MTk=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"oemmes","type":"User","id":6675519,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oemmes\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"NONE","body":"> Sorry, but for me it's not suitable to preload all of the textures. \n\nAll the 3D engines of the modern games do that.\nSome time ago I've made a Sims like WebGL demo for a client.\n256 High-Res (1024x1024) preloaded textures.\nIt runs perfect on a computer with 8GB RAM (with shared 1.5 GB VRAM !).\np.s.\nOf course, if you want to follow another path you're free to do it.\n","created_at":"2016-07-15T12:28:45.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9337#issuecomment-232938895","id":232938895,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9337","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIzMjkzODg5NQ==","updated_at":"2016-07-15T12:29:22.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/232938895","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/10137?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/ghost","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMTM3","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"ghost","type":"User","id":10137,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ghost\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"NONE","body":"You should update the material after the texture has been loaded, e.g. use the `onLoad` callback of the `TextureLoader`. This should take of the flickering.\nNow on the other hand you say the texture should have been cached but isn't? Do you have a fiddle demonstrating that?\n","created_at":"2016-07-17T18:24:13.000Z","